<DOC><DOCNO> AP890608-0089 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-06-08-89 1253EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Yugoslavia-Crime     06-08 0114</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Yugoslavia-Crime,0116</SECOND><HEAD>First Mob Trial Opens in Yugoslavia</HEAD><DATELINE>ZAGREB, Yugoslavia (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Fourteen Yugoslavs went on trialThursday on charges that they were members of an ``American-styleorganized crime gang'' that allegedly operated in this Croatiancapital.   If the men are convicted ``in the first Mafia trial'' incommunist Yugoslavia, ``that would be an official recognition thatorganized crime has taken hold in this country,'' the VecernjeNovosti newspaper said.   The suspects are charged with a series of attempted murders,extortions, intimidations and beatings, published reports said.   The group reportedly offered ``protection'' to several privatenight clubs, restaurants and shops. Owners who rejected the offerwere beaten up and their establishments were destroyed.</TEXT></DOC>